article.headline: Norfolk St. 78, Florida A&amp,M 65
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Michael Deloach scored 25 points, including going 2-for-2 on 3-pointers, leading Norfolk State in a 78-65 win over Florida A&M on Monday night for the Spartans' first Mid-Eastern Conference win of the season. Aleek Pauline added 14 points and Kyle O'Quinn scored eight points and grabbed 13 rebounds for the Spartans (2-12, 1-2), who snapped an 11-game losing skid. The Spartans won for the first time since a 72-71 contest against Maine on Nov. 16. The game was tied at 29-all at the break, but the Spartans outscored the Rattlers 49-36 in the second half to seal the win. Norfolk State outrebounded Florida A&M 42-35. Larry Jackson led the Rattlers (3-12, 1-2) with 16 points, while Christopher Walker had 15 and Yannick Crowder added 10. The Rattlers, who opened the season on a 10-game winning streak, have lost two of three.
